1 (B) A CIRCUIT COURTHOUSE SHALL MAINTAIN ON ITS PREMISES A PRIVATE
2 LACTATION ROOM THAT MAY BE USED BY EMPLOYEES OF THE COURT AND MEMBERS
3 OF THE PUBLIC TO NURSE AND EXPRESS BREAST MILK.
4 (C) THE LACTATION ROOM REQUIRED UNDER THIS SECTION SHALL
5 INCLUDE:
6 (1) A CHAIR WITH A TABLE AND ELECTRICAL OUTLET NEARBY TO
7 ACCOMMODATE PLACEMENT OF A BREAST PUMP DEVICE;
8 (2) A DOOR THAT MAY BE LOCKED FROM THE INSIDE;
9 (3) A SINK; AND
10 (4) A REFRIGERATOR.
11 8–402.
12 (a) Subject to the requirements of this section, a jury judge or, if a county’s jury
13 plan allows, its jury commissioner may disqualify, excuse, or exempt an individual who is
14 summoned for jury service or reschedule jury service.
15 (b) An individual may be disqualified only on the basis of information provided
16 on a juror questionnaire or during an interview or other competent evidence.
17 (c) (1) To be excused, an individual shall show, on a juror questionnaire,
18 during an interview, or by other competent evidence, that [extreme]:
19 (I) EXTREME inconvenience, public necessity, or undue hardship
20 requires excusal;
21 (II) THE INDIVIDUAL IS A BREAST–FEEDING MOTHER; OR
22 (III) THE INDIVIDUAL HAS LEGAL CUSTODY OF AND IS
23 PERSONALLY RESPONSIBLE FOR A CHILD UNDER THE AGE OF 4 YEARS REQUIRING
24 CONTINUOUS CARE BY THE INDIVIDUAL DURING NORMAL COURT HOURS.
25 (2) An individual may be excused:
26 (i) Only for the period that the jury judge or jury commissioner
27 considers necessary; and
28 (ii) Not more than twice unless the jury judge finds that the
29 individual has shown an extraordinary circumstance that requires an additional excuse.

